  "description": [
    "THE RING FIGHT THAT GAVE PEACE TO PIEDMONT SECTION ENDED INDIAN INTERFERENCE Placing of Tablet on Hill at Tamassee Recently Com memorated an Important Event in History of Sec tion GEN ANDREW PICKENS AND HIS PATRIOTS Thought They Were Facing Certain Death and Possi ble Extinction at Hands of Savage Chevokees A Tablet Now Marks Loca tion of Famous Fight Several weeks ago the Wizard of Tamasce Chapter Daughters of the American Revolution had placed on an eminence near the Tones home stead a bronze tablet set in a boulder of native granite marking the site of the famous Ring Fight or Ring Battle which was engaged in by Gen Andrew Pickens and his followers in conflict with the Cherokee Indianswho were giving the white settlers at that time no end of trouble and at times threatened extinction for the brave sturdy white settlers who were endea voring to carve out a peaceful home land in the heart of the then wilder ness and in territory long held in un disputed sovereignty of the Red Man Incident to the unveiling of the tab let commemorative of the last stub born stand made by the Cherokees and the signal victory won"
  ],
